Paper: hep-th/9403087

Date: 1994-03-16

Title: Cosmological Surrealism

Authors: Yuval Ne'eman

Comments: 7 pages, TAUP N237

Journal-ref: Found. Phys. Lett. 7 (1994) 483-488

Inflationary Cosmology makes the universe ``eternal" and provides forrecurrent universe creation, ad infinitum -- making it also plausible to assumethat ``our" Big Bang was also preceeded by others, etc.. However, GR tells usthat in the ``parent" universe's reference frame, the newborn universe'sexpansion will never start. Our picture of ``reality" in spacetime has to beenlarged.